1
00:00:02,674 --> 00:00:05,908
This is an easy one.
You love this guy.

2
00:00:05,910 --> 00:00:07,677
Me.

3
00:00:08,813 --> 00:00:12,215
Come on, he's an
underappreciated genius.

4
00:00:12,217 --> 00:00:14,684
Still think it's me.

5
00:00:14,686 --> 00:00:16,285
It's not you.

6
00:00:16,287 --> 00:00:18,988
Now think, there's
a car named after him.

7
00:00:18,990 --> 00:00:20,223
Of course there is.

8
00:00:20,225 --> 00:00:22,325
The Mini Cooper,
'cause it's me.

9
00:00:24,562 --> 00:00:26,429
How about this:

10
00:00:26,431 --> 00:00:28,564
he's a poor man's
Sheldon Cooper.

11
00:00:28,566 --> 00:00:30,199
Oh, Tesla.

12
00:00:31,002 --> 00:00:32,068
- Hi.
- Hey! - Hello.

13
00:00:32,070 --> 00:00:33,603
How'd it go?
Oh, not fun.

14
00:00:33,605 --> 00:00:36,772
The doctor shoved a camera
up into my sinuses.

15
00:00:36,774 --> 00:00:38,908
Yeah, I watched. It was like
the scary boat tunnel

16
00:00:38,910 --> 00:00:41,010
in<i> Willy Wonka.</i>

17
00:00:42,313 --> 00:00:44,380
Did they figure out what's wrong?
Yeah.

18
00:00:44,382 --> 00:00:45,348
It's a deviated septum.

19
00:00:45,350 --> 00:00:46,482
The surgery
to correct it is simple.

20
00:00:46,484 --> 00:00:47,683
He's gonna do it next week.

21
00:00:47,685 --> 00:00:49,619
Why would you have surgery?

22
00:00:49,621 --> 00:00:51,320
Because I can't breathe.

23
00:00:51,322 --> 00:00:53,823
I snore, I get sinus
infections...

24
00:00:53,825 --> 00:00:56,325
Yeah, back off,
he's all mine.

25
00:00:56,327 --> 00:00:58,594
But you don't have
a life-threatening condition.

26
00:00:58,596 --> 00:01:00,496
Why would you
take the risk of surgery?

27
00:01:00,498 --> 00:01:02,298
Sheldon, it's a routine
procedure.

28
00:01:02,300 --> 00:01:04,400
I've heard you complain
about his snoring.

29
00:01:04,402 --> 00:01:06,602
We... Yes, for the first
five or six years,

30
00:01:06,604 --> 00:01:08,504
but I've gotten used to it.

31
00:01:09,107 --> 00:01:10,506
It helps me sleep.

32
00:01:10,508 --> 00:01:13,176
He's like my mucus-powered
white noise machine.

33
00:01:14,412 --> 00:01:16,345
Sheldon, I'm gonna get
the surgery, it's no big deal.

34
00:01:16,347 --> 00:01:17,446
End of story.

35
00:01:17,448 --> 00:01:18,995
Very well.
I'm done talking about it.

36
00:01:18,995 --> 00:01:19,812
Thank you.

37
00:01:19,836 --> 00:01:21,451
I believe it was
your turn in the game.

38
00:01:21,452 --> 00:01:22,785
Okay.

39
00:01:24,589 --> 00:01:25,621
Let's see...

40
00:01:25,623 --> 00:01:28,391
Oh, this person is most famous

41
00:01:28,393 --> 00:01:29,559
for never having gotten

42
00:01:29,561 --> 00:01:32,495
his nose mutilated
with elective surgery

43
00:01:32,497 --> 00:01:34,997
and never living the rest
of his life in the shadows

44
00:01:34,999 --> 00:01:36,832
as a hideous, disfigured freak.

45
00:01:38,136 --> 00:01:40,436
I think you could
give a better clue.

46
00:01:40,438 --> 00:01:41,537
I don't.

47
00:01:41,539 --> 00:01:44,740
I'm not even sure if
that's a person or a typo.

48
00:01:45,810 --> 00:01:49,078
? Our whole universe
was in a hot, dense state ?

49
00:01:49,080 --> 00:01:52,748
? Then nearly 14 billion years
ago expansion started... Wait! ?

50
00:01:52,750 --> 00:01:54,350
? The Earth began to cool ?

51
00:01:54,352 --> 00:01:56,886
? The autotrophs began to drool,
Neanderthals developed tools ?

52
00:01:56,888 --> 00:01:59,455
? We built the Wall ?
?<i> We built the pyramids</i> ?

53
00:01:59,457 --> 00:02:02,191
? Math, Science, History,
unraveling the mystery ?

54
00:02:02,193 --> 00:02:04,093
? That all started
with a big bang ?

55
00:02:04,095 --> 00:02:04,513
?<i> Bang!</i> ?

